{"id":3090,"date":"2020-08-18T18:52:12","date_gmt":"2020-08-18T22:52:12","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.globalempowermentmission.org\/?page_id=3090"},"modified":"2022-06-30T11:34:04","modified_gmt":"2022-06-30T15:34:04","slug":"our-story","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.globalempowermentmission.org\/about\/our-story\/","title":{"rendered":"Our Story"},"content":{"rendered":"\t\t<div data-elementor-type=\"wp-page\" data-elementor-id=\"3090\" class=\"elementor elementor-3090\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-1f34222b elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"1f34222b\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;gradient&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-18026800\" data-id=\"18026800\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c7ae4bf elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"c7ae4bf\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h3 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Global Empowerment Mission is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization founded in 2011 as a first responder to global disasters.<\/h3>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-47dc7a7 elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"47dc7a7\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img width=\"800\" height=\"95\" src=\"https:\/\/www.globalempowermentmission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/branded-divider-1024x122.png\" class=\"attachment-large size-large\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.globalempowermentmission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/branded-divider-1024x122.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.globalempowermentmission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/branded-divider-600x72.png 600w, https:\/\/www.globalempowermentmission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/branded-divider-300x36.png 300w, https:\/\/www.globalempowermentmission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/branded-divider-768x92.png 768w, https:\/\/www.globalempowermentmission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/branded-divider-1536x184.png 1536w, https:\/\/www.globalempowermentmission.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/08\/branded-divider-2048x245.png 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-61d7457b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"61d7457b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>The organization\u2019s journey began with grassroots community engagement as its founder, Michael Capponi, and board members have been involved in supporting some of the most significant global tragedies. For two decades, the team has assisted in over 300 missions around the world starting with the 1999 Kosovo Crisis and most recently Ukraine. Please view <a href=\"https:\/\/www.globalempowermentmission.org\/missions\/\">our missions page<\/a> for more info.<\/p><p>Following the completion of immediate response, and recognizing the continued need for support, GEM began to bridge the gap between first response and sustainable development. In 2017, GEM began operating Bethenny Frankel\u2019s #BStrong initiative, which fills this need by supplying unrestricted cash card distributions allowing beneficiaries to meet their individual needs. This partnership disrupts disaster response while activating and influencing the global community by going above and beyond real time emergency assistance to individuals and their families.<\/p><p>With the objective of minimizing the duration of time communities are stuck in the gap, and aiming to complete the cycle of disaster response, GEM instituted its sustainable development programming by building and rebuilding homes, schools and communities while establishing livelihood initiatives. GEM has been able to reduce what was an initial three year sustainability cycle in Haiti to a refined approach that resulted in a one year sustainability cycle in the Bahamas.<\/p><p>To date, GEM has supported missions in 40 countries, all 50 US states, and territories including the Caribbean. The organizations complete 360 degree response results in having a long-lasting institutional impact.<\/p><p>\u00a0<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-23fee74 elementor-section-height-min-height elementor-section-items-top elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"23fee74\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-477d644\" data-id=\"477d644\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c344ca4 elementor-align-center elementor-widget elementor-widget-button\" data-id=\"c344ca4\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"button.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-wi